<div><h3>PSCI 214 - Mass Murder and Genocide Under Communism </h3>  <hr>Is communism inherently genocidal? Do communism and mass murder necessarily go hand in hand? This course explores the origins, motivations and consequences of the brutal and deadly policies adopted in three very different communist regimes (the Soviet Union, China and Cambodia). We will also consider potential ways to avert mass killing and genocide.<br><br><strong>Anticipated Terms Offered:</strong> Offered every year<br><br></div>		</td>
